  "text": "There are two basic approaches to anomaly detection using system calls; sequence-based approach and frequency-based approach. The former approach keeps track of system call sequences in a database of normal behavior. The latter drops the order of the system calls while keeping the frequency of occurrence of each distinct system call. By not storing order information of the system call sequence, frequency-based techniques requires much less storage space while providing better performance and accuracy [CITATION_1] .",
